STEP 1: Set Up MySQL Database
Open MySQL Workbench (or any MySQL tool you prefer).

Create a database called taskmaster.

CREATE DATABASE taskmaster;

Make sure the database credentials in application.properties are correct. For example:

spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/taskmaster
spring.datasource.username=root
spring.datasource.password=Sid@123*


The tables will be created automatically when the application starts if you're using Spring Data JPA.

Step 4: Run the Application
The application will start running on http://localhost:8080.

How to Use the API
1. User Registration

Endpoint: /api/register

Method: POST

Description: Register a new user.



Response:

Status: 200 OK

Message: "User registered successfully"
2. User Authentication (Login)

Endpoint: /api/authenticate

Method: POST

Description: Log in with the registered username and password. Returns a JWT token.

Response:

Status: 200 OK

Body: JWT token as a string.

Example: "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJqb2huX2RvZSIsImV4cCI6MTY3MzA1OTg3Mn0.CnVjqRtQfdiF4beA1vbu0MrTLU5DbblQenjlbbq3p8E"

Create a Project

1. Create Task (POST)

Endpoint: /api/tasks

Method: POST
Description: Create a new project.



Get All Projects

Endpoint: /api/projects

Method: GET

Description: Retrieve all the projects for the authenticated user.

Update Task (PUT)

Endpoint: /api/tasks/{id}

Method: PUT

Path Variable: id (Example: 1)

Delete Task (DELETE)

Endpoint: /api/tasks/{id}

Method: DELETE

Path Variable: id (Example: 1)

Error Handling

Invalid requests (e.g., missing fields, incorrect data) will return an error with appropriate status codes and messages.

Contributing

Feel free to open issues or pull requests to improve the API. Any suggestions or improvements are welcome!

